  "prompt": "Kindly suggest the best NPTE classes in NY?",
  "response": "When looking for the best NPTE (National Physical Therapy Exam) preparatory classes in New York, consider the following options that are often highly regarded:\n\n1. **Kaplan Test Prep**: Known for its comprehensive review courses and practice exams, Kaplan offers NPTE preparation tailored to help students succeed.\n\n2. **Scorebuilders**: This is a popular choice among physical therapy students. They provide review courses that include lectures, practice questions, and study materials specifically for the NPTE.\n\n3. **TherapyEd**: This organization offers an extensive review course that includes lectures, practice questions, and interactive sessions. Their study materials are well-structured for NPTE preparation.\n\n4. **PT Final Exam**: They offer a variety of resources, including online videos, practice exams, and study guides, which can be very helpful for NPTE preparation.\n\n5. **APTA (American Physical Therapy Association)**: While they don't offer specific classes, they provide valuable resources, study guides, and access to practice exams that can aid in your preparation.\n\n6. **Local universities**: Some universities in New York may offer NPTE review courses or workshops. Check with institutions that have physical therapy programs, as they often have resources available.\n\nIt's a good idea to read reviews, check course formats (online vs. in-person), and see what materials and support they offer. Additionally, consider joining local study groups for peer support.",
